  <div id="tribute-info">
    <h3>The Rise Of Conor McGregor</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>2013: Perfect start</strong> - McGregor records a first-round TKO over Marcus Brimage in 67 seconds on April 6, 2013.
  <li><strong>2014: "WE'RE HERE TO TAKE OVER"</strong> - McGregor tears his ACL in a unanimous decision win over Max Holloway on Aug. 17, 2013.
       <li><strong>2014: "The Wolrd Title Is Next"</strong> - McGregor scores a first-round TKO of Dustin Poirier on Sept. 27, 2014.
      <li><strong>2015: "FIRST TASTE OF GOLD"</strong> -  McGregor scores a second-round TKO of Chad Mendes for the interim featherweight belt on July 11, 2015.</li>
      <li><strong>2015: "Featherweight CHAMP"</strong> - It is McGregor's fifth consecutive win by knockout and is the fastest finish in the history of UFC title fights.
  <li><strong>2016: "MAKING HISTORY"</strong> - McGregor becomes the first UFC fighter to hold belts in two weight classes simultaneously as he destroys Eddie Alvarez on Nov. 12, 2016. </li> 
      
    </ul>
    
    <i>"Who the F**K IS THAT GUY."  </i> <br><br>
    <i>"- Conor McGregor"</i> 
